\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. N. jonquilla} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 290 (1753). Leaves 2-4 mm wide. Flowers 22-32 mm in diameter, in umbels of 2-5. Pedicels 15-50 mm at anthesis, shorter or longer than the spathe. Hypanthial tube (17-)20-30 mm, straight. Perianth-segments 10-15 mm, patent. Corona 3-5 × 9-15 mm. 2n = 14. {\i Meadows and damp places. • C. & S. Spain, S. & E. Portugal; widely cultivated for its perfume, and naturalized elsewhere in S.Europe.} Hs Lu [Ga It Ju.]
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. N. requienii} M. J. Roemer,{\i  Syn. Monogr.}{\b  4}: 236 (1847) ({\i N. juncifolius} auct., non Salisb., nec Lag.,{\i  N. pallens} Freyn ex Willk.). Leaves 1-2 mm wide. Flowers 16-22 mm in diameter, solitary or in pairs. Pedicels 11-22 mm at anthesis, shorter than spathe. Hypanthial tube 12-18(-20) mm, straight. Perianth-segments 7-10 mm, patent. Corona 4-6 × 10-17 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Rocky hillsides and meadows. • S. France, S. & E. Spain.} ?Co Ga Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  Plants recently reported from Sardegna are like {\b 9} but with leaves up to 4·5 mm wide and corona not more than 7 mm wide. They require further investigation.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. N. willkommii} (Samp.) A. Fernandes,{\i  Bol. Soc. Brot.} ser. 2, {\b 40}: 213 (1966) ({\i N. jonquilloides} Willk., non Willd. ex Schultes fil.). Leaves 2-3 mm wide, somewhat glaucous, erect. Flowers 14-19 mm in diameter, in umbels of 2-3. Pedicels 20-45 mm at anthesis, the longest exceeding the spathe. Hypanthial tube 11-15 mm, straight. Perianth-segments 6-9 mm, patent. Corona 4-5 × 7-11 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Damp grassland. • S. Portugal, S.W. Spain.} Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. N. gaditanus} Boiss. & Reuter in Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov}.{\b  3}({\b 4}): 96 (1859) (incl.{\i  N. minutiflorus} Willk.). Leaves 1-2 mm wide, usually procumbent. Flowers 10-20 mm in diameter, in umbels of 2-5(-8), rarely solitary. Pedicels 13-35 mm at anthesis, usually shorter than spathe. Hypanthial tube 8-17 mm, usually curved. Perianth-segments 4-9 mm, patent or deflexed. Corona 2·5-7 × 4·5-8 mm. 2n = 14, 21. •{\i  S. Portugal, S. Spain. }Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  N. fernandesii} G. Pedro,{\i  Bol. Soc. Brot.} ser. 2, {\b 21}: 60 (1947), is known from two populations in S.C. Portugal; somewhat similar plants are found in S.W. Spain. It is in most characters intermediate between {\b 10} and {\b 11}; its taxonomic status is obscure.
\par

