\pard\f0\fs28    ({\b 12-15}). {\b N. rupicola} group. Bulb 15-22 × 8-18 mm. Leaves 8-30 cm × 1·5-5 mm, more or less glaucous, canaliculate and with 2 keels on the convex surface, or rarely 4-angled. Spathe 15-35 mm, scarious, tubular below, open above. Flowers solitary or in umbels of 2-5, 13-30 mm in diameter, seldom strongly fragrant, deep yellow, concolorous. Pedicels 1-15 mm. Hypanthial tube 10-25 mm, narrowly cylindrical. Perianth-segments 7-14 × 5-11 mm, patent or slightly deflexed. Corona 2-8 × 5-10 mm, entire or lobed.
\par

