\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. N. rupicola} Dufour in Schultes & Schultes fil.,{\i  Syst. Veg. }{\b 7}: 958 (1830). Leaves 1·5-3 mm wide, erect to decumbent, with 2 dorsal keels; margin smooth. Spathe 20-35 mm, tubular for c. ¾ of its length. Flowers 15-30 mm in diameter, solitary. Pedicel absent, rarely up to 3 mm. Hypanthial tube (13-)18-25 mm. Perianth-segments 7-13 × 5-10 mm. Corona 2-5 × 7-10 mm, at least twice as wide as long, subentire to conspicuously 6-lobed. All stamens included. 2n = 14.{\i  Rock-crevices and stony mountain pastures; calcifuge. • C. Spain, N. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. N. cuatrecasasii} Casas, Laínz & Ruiz Rejón, {\i Cuad. Ci. Biol. Granada}{\b  2}: 4 (1973) ({\i N. rupicola }subsp. {\i pedunculatus} (Cuatrec.) Laínz ex Meikle). Leaves 2·5-4·5 mm wide, erect, with 2 dorsal keels; margin smooth. Spathe 20-25 mm, tubular for c. ¼ of its length. Flowers 22-30 mm in diameter, solitary (rarely in pairs). Pedicel (6-)9-12 mm. Hypanthial tube (10-)12-15 mm. Perianth-segments 9-12 × 7-11 mm. Corona 4-6 × 8-10 mm, 1¾-2 times as wide as long; margin entire or crenulate. Upper whorl of stamens slightly exserted. 2n = 14.{\i  Rock crevices; calcicole. • Mountains of C. & S. Spain.} Hs.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. N. calcicola} Mendonca, {\i Bol. Soc. Brot.} ser. 2, {\b 6}: 318 (1930). Leaves 2-5 mm wide, erect, with 2 dorsal keels; margins smooth. Spathe 16-25 mm, tubular for c. ¼ of its length. Flowers 17-25 (-33) mm in diameter, in umbels of (1-)2-5. Pedicels 6-15 mm. Hypanthial tube 13-18 mm. Perianth-segments 7-10(-14) × 5-8 mm. Corona 4-8 × 6-9 mm, only slightly wider than long; margin obscurely crenulate. Upper whorl of stamens exserted. 2n = 14.{\i  Crevices of limestone rocks. • W.C. Portugal.} Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. N. scaberulus} Henriq., {\i Bol. Soc. Brot.}{\b  6}: 45 (1888). Leaves 1-3·5 mm wide, usually decumbent, with 2 dorsal keels; margin usually minutely scabrid. Spathe 15-20 mm, tubular for c. ¼ of its length. Flowers 12-17 mm in diameter, solitary or in umbels of 2-3. Pedicels 8-15 mm. Hypanthial tube 12-17 mm. Perianth-segments 4·5-7 × 3-5 mm. Corona 2-5 × 5-7 mm, usually 1½-2 times as wide as long; margin entire or crenulate. Upper whorl of stamens exserted. 2n = 14.{\i  Rocky places. • N.C. Portugal }({\i Mondego valley}). Lu.
\par

